abstract: Bipartisan group of senators propose bill to permanently end all American travel restrictions to Cuba; bill will not eliminate trade embargo, and will likely be contested in Congress.
lead_paragraph: A bipartisan group of lawmakers has taken the first step in a looming congressional battle over how far to expand trade and tourism with the Castro government.

headline.main: Group of Senators Seeks to Lift Cuba Travel Limits
